  <prompt>
    Author `FileClassificationService` (NEW) in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/` (or `Services/Ai/Files/`). Uses `gpt-4o-mini` via the existing `IOpenAiClient` facade to classify uploaded file content into `{ documentType, confidence }` per architecture §6.1. Target latency: ~250ms (parallel path with 068, 069). Returns `FileClassificationResult { string DocumentType, double Confidence }`. Strict ADR-015 tier-1 logging — NEVER log file content or the classification text.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in Azure OpenAI structured-output classification + ADR-013 AI facade boundary + ADR-015 tier-1 logging.</role>

  <goal>
    `FileClassificationService.cs` exists with `IFileClassificationService` interface + `ClassifyAsync(string textContent, string fileName, string contentType, CancellationToken ct) → FileClassificationResult`. Implementation calls gpt-4o-mini with structured-output prompt asking for `documentType` (e.g., "NDA", "patent", "invoice", "contract", "other") + `confidence` (0.0–1.0). Returns the parsed result.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture §4.4 + §6.1 (Upload pipeline). One of three parallel enrichment services orchestrated by `SessionFileEnrichmentService` (066). The `documentType` output flows into the layered context card (task 076) and is later consumed by WP2 file-aware routing (Phase 5 Hybrid C pre-filter — FR-17). Confidence enables downstream confidence-based routing decisions.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/IOpenAiClient.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/OpenAiClient.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Chat/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Service lives INSIDE the AI module (`Services/Ai/`). MAY consume `IOpenAiClient` directly — this is NOT CRUD code. CRUD code consuming this service must go through `PublicContracts/`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Optional: cache classification result per (sha256 of textContent, contentType) for 5 min — only if hot-path benchmark justifies; otherwise skip caching for v1.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Tier-1 logging only: fileId, sessionId, durationMs, resultDocumentType (the LABEL is safe — it's a discrete category), confidence value. NEVER log textContent (input) or any free-text from the LLM response beyond the discrete label.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task publish-size measurement; new service should add &lt;0.5 MB.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture §6.1">Uses `gpt-4o-mini` (NOT gpt-4o); structured output preferred (JSON schema). Target latency ~250ms parallel.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No new external API (no Document Intelligence per CLAUDE.md "MUST NOT add new external API surface"). Use existing Azure OpenAI client only.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md</file>
